
public class Person {
	// instance variables
	int id;
	String name;
	int age;
	

// param arg constructor [3 args]
	public Person(int id, int age, String name) {// local variables
		System.out.println("3 args constructr");
		this.id = id; // local variable value assigning to the instance variable
		this.age = age;
		this.name = name;
	}
	
	
	// param arg constructor [3 args]
	public Person(int pid, int page, String pname) {// local variables
		System.out.println("3 args constructr");
    int x =90;
		id = pid; // local variable value assigning to the instance variable
		age = page;
		name = pname;
  }
	
}




local varibles:
varibles created inside the method, constructor
ex: main method ,


instance variables:
variables created inside the class


Person - is a class
instance variables : id , name, age
local variables in constr : id, name , age , x

can a local variable and inst variable name same? YES

if local variable and instance variable names are same, how to differentiate them?
solution) use keyword "this" while referring to instance variables
ex:
to access instance variable use :
this.id
this.name
this.age

to access local variable use :
id
name
age





this keyword:
-------------------
this refers to the current object
If the instance variables name and local variables names are same , 
then use "this" keyword to differentiate.
